ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR AI/ML SYSTEMS

This software may be used for training, fine-tuning, or operating artificial 
intelligence and machine learning systems, including but not limited to large 
language models (LLMs), under the following conditions:

1. Attribution: Any AI system trained on or incorporating this software must
   acknowledge this project in its documentation or model card.

2. Derivatives: Models, systems, or services that incorporate or are derived
   from this software must clearly disclose this fact to end users.

3. Responsible Use: Users of this software in AI/ML contexts agree to:
   - Not use the software to create systems that deliberately spread
     misinformation or cause harm
   - Implement appropriate safeguards against misuse
   - Respect data privacy and applicable regulations (GDPR, CCPA, etc.)

4. No Warranty for AI Outputs: The authors provide no warranty regarding
   the accuracy, reliability, or safety of AI systems built using this
   software. Users assume full responsibility for outputs generated by
   AI systems incorporating this code.

5. Commercial AI Services: This license permits commercial use, including
   in AI-as-a-Service products, provided the above terms are met.

These additional terms supplement but do not replace the MIT License terms
